## **Month 1 ‚Äì PLC Foundations (Weeks 1‚Äì4)**

**Course:** [PLC Essential Training (Siemens S7-1200) ‚Äì LinkedIn Learning](https://www.linkedin.com/learning/plc-essential-training-siemens-s7-1200)
**Hours/week:** ~5‚Äì6h
**Certificate:** LinkedIn Learning (included)

| Week | Focus                     | Task / Mini-Project                                                                                                                           |
| ---- | ------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| 1    | PLC basics, I/O concepts  | Set up virtual PLC (OpenPLC or Siemens LOGO! Soft Comfort). Practice basic I/O simulation (on/off switches).                                  |
| 2    | Ladder Logic fundamentals | Create simple ladder logic programs (motor start/stop, traffic lights). Document screenshots in GitHub.                                       |
| 3    | Sensors & actuators       | Simulate temperature sensor ‚Üí PLC ‚Üí output control (LED or fan). Write a short report describing data flow.                                   |
| 4    | Mini capstone             | Combine previous lessons: design a **small room control system** using PLC simulation. Test it fully and commit code/documentation to GitHub. |

